Package: peditools
Title: Pediatric Clinical Data Science Tools
Date: 2025-01-08
Version: 0.3.1.00
Authors@R: person("Joseph", "Chou", email = "joe.nicu@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A collection of tools for newborn and pediatric anthropometric calculations
    and data abstraction from Vermont Oxford Network registry exports. Includes charts
    based on Lambda, Mu, Sigma (LMS) parameters, including: Fenton 2003,
    Olsen 2010, Olsen BMI, CDC infant, CDC pediatric, CDC BMI, CDC (Addo) skin, WHO infant,
    WHO skin, Abdel-Rahman 2017, Mramba 2017, Zemel Down Syndrome, Brooks cerebral palsy,
    WHO expanded, Cappa 2024 (except BMI). Includes functions to take a Vermont Oxford
    Network XML or CSV data file export read into a data frame, converting the coded
    variables into human readable factors.
Depends:
    R (>= 3.5.0)
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.1.0
Imports:
    stats
Suggests:
    testthat,
    car,
